    <h1 id="help">Help!</h1>

    <p>
      If you need help when running AC, follow these steps:
    </p>

    <ol>
      <li>
        Search this documentation for a solution, make sure you read the relevant sections.
      </li>
      <li>
        Try some of the <a href="#online resources">online resources</a>. Especially the 
        <a href="http://assault.cubers.net/wiki/" target="_blank">AssaultCube wiki</a>, which contains user
        created content. You may find the wiki's <a href="http://assault.cubers.net/wiki/FAQ" target="_blank">FAQ</a> to be handy.
      </li>
      <li>
        Visit the <a href="http://assault.cubers.net/forum" target="_blank">AssaultCube forum</a> and use its 
        <a href="http://assault.cubers.net/forum/search.php" target="_blank">search</a> functionality. If you 
        don't find any useful stuff, post a detailed question there. Please be respectful and follow the forum
        rules.
      </li>
      <li>
        Visit the <a href="http://www.cubeengine.com/forum.php4" target="_blank">Cube Engine forum</a>. Although 
        most things discussed in these forums may be irrelevant, AssaultCube is based from Cube, so someone may 
        have an answer there. Make sure you use its search functionality first before posting a detailed question 
        there. Please respect their forum rules.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <p>
      Instead of posting to the forum, you can also ask the people in our IRC channel: <a href="irc://quakenet/assaultcube">#assaultcube</a> on <a href="http://staff.quakenet.org/servers.phtml" target="_blank">Quakenet</a>.
    </p>

